main event: A UFO sighting occurred on July 16, 1965 in Presto, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The object was described as an oval, multi-colored object with a green predominant color and antenna-like wires on the side.
The object was observed at a very low altitude, between 50 to 100 feet, and moved in a straight line too slowly to be an aircraft.
Radar data from a Pittsburgh weather report may have detected a related event around the same time.
The object was brighter than a star.
result: The sighting was concluded to be an aircraft, with the analysis stating the data was very poor.
sighted object: An oval, multi-colored object with antenna-like wires
